":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish and northern Irish: habitational name from the districtnear Dumbarton, recorded in 1174 in the form <i>Leuenaichs</i> and inthe following year as <i>Levenax</i>. Apparently it is named fromGaelic <i>leamhan</i> ‘elm’ + the locative suffix <i>-ach</i> +English <i>-s</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Lenox","meanings":["Scottish and northern Irish: variant of   Lennox  ."]}]},{"name":"Domhnall","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Gaelic: from Old Celtic <i>dubno</i> ‘world’ + <i>val</i> ‘rule’.  See also  <b>Donald</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Domhnall of Lennox - Earl of Lennox was born in 1290, in Balloch Castle, Dunbartonshire, Scotland, United Kingdom, his father, Earl Maol Choluim Lennox 5th Earl of Lennox, was 21 and his mother, Lady De Mar, was 21. He had at least 1 daughter with Lady Margaret. He died on 19 July 1333, in Scotland, at the age of 43."},"et":{"1290–19 July 1333":"1290–19. juuli 1333","1290–1333":"1290–1333","1302–Male":"1302–Surnud","1290–Female":"1290–Surnud","1320–1388":"1320–1388","1270–1333":"1270–1333","1270–Female":"1270–Surnud","19 July 1333":"19. juuli 1333","1302":"1302","1388":"1388","1333":"1333","1320":"1320","from 1333 to 1365":"1333 kuni 1365","about 1320":"umbes 1320","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","Balloch Castle, Loch Lomond, Dunbartonshire, Scotland":"Scotland","Halidon Hill, Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, England"},"fi":{"1290–19 July 1333":"1290–19. heinäkuuta 1333","1290–1333":"1290–1333","1302–Male":"1302–Kuollut","1290–Female":"1290–Kuollut","1320–1388":"1320–1388","1270–1333":"1270–1333","1270–Female":"1270–Kuollut","19 July 1333":"19. heinäkuuta 1333","1302":"1302","1388":"1388","1333":"1333","1320":"1320","from 1333 to 1365":"vuodesta 1333 vuoteen 1365","about 1320":"noin 1320","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","Ball